page.title: 18ROADS, HIGH WYCOMBE
page.content: The High Street is about fifteen metres wide with a footpath at either side for pedestrians to walk along. It has a white line down the centre,to tell the{motorists}that they can not over-take.A dotted line which means in the country areas that the driver can over-take.There are yellow lines by the side of the road which show parking restrictions. A Dual Carriage Way up Marlow Hill is a{road}divided by a central barrier with two lanes of traffic in each direction. Motorways at the top of Marlow High Street is a big island where the{M40}Motorway passes under the{ road.The Motorway is a special kind of Dual Carriage way on which traffic is allowed to drive faster.The M40 runs between London and Oxford.You must enter and leave at special points.
